title: Central Florida Adventures: Audubon Center for Birds of Prey
text:
By Jon Busdeker contact the reporter Audubon Center for Birds of Prey offers close-up look at owls, eagles 
Opened since 1979, the Audubon Center for Birds of Prey in Maitland is one of Central Florida's best-kept secrets. 
Opened since 1979, the Audubon Center for Birds of Prey in Maitland is one of Central Florida's best-kept secrets. The Audubon Center for Birds of Prey is one of Maitland's best-kept secrets See owls and eagles up-close at the Audubon Center for Birds of Prey in Maitland 
The Audubon Center for Birds of Prey is one of my favorite spots in all of Central Florida. 
Tucked away in Maitland, it's one of those places I tell out-of-towners to check out when they need a day or two away from Orlando's theme parks. But I also run into locals who have never heard of the Center, so I make sure to introduce them to it. 
"We're off the beaten path, but we really give a good sense of older Florida," said the Center's program manager Katie Warner.
